post_text:
At the August 25 monthly Board Meeting, Superintendent Betze provided an update on the reopening of schools. After much consternation and deliberation, the decision has been made for our students in grades 6-12 to go fully remote until Monday, October 12, 2020. Pk-5 will remain in the hybrid/ 100% remote model as detailed in our reopening plan. Additionally, our self contained students' schedules in Pk-12 will not be altered by this decision.

To read Superintendent Betze's full communication on the change to the reopening plan, visit our Roadmap Back to School page on the district website.

To read Superintendent Betze's full communication on the change to the reopening plan, visit our Roadmap Back to School page on the district website.

In an effort to better assist families, we have created the Rville Family Remote Learning Support website. Visit the website to explore the many tutorials on platforms such as Google Classroom, Zoom, Seesaw, as well as applications for specific grade levels and/or content areas. We encourage both hybrid and remote families to explore the resources with their students and bookmark this site for future reference. The website link can also be accessed through our district page under the Curriculum Department.

A special thanks to RHS Media Center Specialist, Gina Policastro, and Liane Balevski, 3rd-grade teacher, for helping to put this together.

https://sites.google.com/rvilleschools.org/rville-family-remote-learning/home

You could win some the 50 raffled baskets!

Please don't forget to support the Class of 2021 for the rescheduled Trivia Night, a Red Carpet & Post Prom Fundraising event! You are now able to pre-purchase raffle tickets and do NOT need to be present/online to win! This LIVE VIRTUAL event will draw the winning tickets for the 50 donated baskets on Monday, August 17 at 7:00 pm. Due to the continued restrictions because of COVID, there will NOT be a 50/50 and NO trivia games will be played.

Tickets are $20 for 10 raffle tickets. Must be 18 or older to participate. 50 donated baskets will be raffled! All proceeds benefit the Class of 2021 Red Carpet and a safe, alcohol and drug-free Post Prom event. Please support this event by Sunday, August 16 at midnight! Here is the link: https://go.rallyup.com/trivia-night-2021.

If you have any questions, contact Jhansi Sadula at jhalaks@yahoo.com or 609-371-0302 or Kristina Jaoude at kjaoude@yahoo.com or 609-933-4063.

post_text: The Robbinsville Board of Education will hold their annual Goal Setting Meeting tomorrow, July 22 at 6pm. This is an in-person meeting and will be held in the Robbinsville High School Auditorium; the public is welcome to attend. We will be following government social distancing guidelines and masks are required while in the building. To view the meeting agenda, please visit the Robbinsville School District website. We look forward to hearing the communities feedback and thoughts.

post_text:
The health and safety of our students and staff is always our top priority. As we work to define the best plan for our district, we undoubtedly know that school will look very different this fall. Parents who have thoughts, comments or questions about the Robbinsville School District re-opening plan are encouraged to email us at:

reopenquestions@robbinsville.k12.nj.us.

Emails will be answered within 24 hours and all questions and answers will be posted to our website.

post_text:
A message from Superintendent Betze and the Robbinsville BOE...

"On behalf of the Robbinsville Board of Education...Congratulations to you on your graduation from Robbinsville High School, in spite of a pandemic, virtual learning, social distancing, and mask-wearing...you made it!

"From the BoE members who are unable to be present in order to comply with the Governor’s directive on crowd limits...we sincerely wish we could be present to honor the Class of 2020...you’ve made us proud.

"Good luck in all your future endeavors…"

post_text: Road Trip! Give Mr. Patterson a steering wheel and a direction to travel..."My favorite summer activity is road tripping in the Midwest or Western USA. Why? You can't get a true feel for what the United States really is by flying over it. There is something special about eating lunch in a town whose population is 500. When the speed limit is 80 and you can see to the horizon in all directions, it is very relaxing. Likewise, when it's the middle of the summer, but the temperature is 37 because your in the middle of 8000-10000 foot tall mountains, you can't beat it." #RvilleProud

Here Comes The Sun by the Beatles was written by George Harrison after what he called “a very long winter that went on forever.” The Robbinsville Board of Education and the administrative team recognize the ongoing world events effecting all of us. We offer this video as a way to lighten your spirits as we traverse this long winter and look toward the promise of a bright future for our students, families, staff and all members of the Robbinsville Public School community.

We extend special thanks to Kevin & Felicity Holt, our video producers!

post_text:
A message from Team Nemesis 2590...

Hello from Nemesis 2590, the Robbinsville High School FIRST Robotics Competition team!!

While at home practicing social distancing, students are always looking for fun things to do. We've assembled a set of STEM-focused engineering challenges that you can do at home using readily available materials. We're calling this Virtual Discovery Day and all the details on our web site: http://frc2590.org/virtualdday/. The challenges are great for all grade levels (2nd through 8th grades).

Make sure to get your parents permission before starting a challenge. We'd love to see what cool solutions you come up with! Please do create a video of your solution and post it (again, with you parents permission) on our Facebook page. All the details are at http://frc2590.org/virtualdday/. We'll pick our favorite solutions and feature them on the web site!

Stay safe and have fun!!!

Team 2590, Nemesis

post_text: Please be advised that Robbinsville Public Schools will close tomorrow, March 13, 2020, for staff development. Teachers will use the day for lesson planning in the event that additional school closure is necessary. All after school activities scheduled for this afternoon and tomorrow are cancelled. The Robbinsville Extended Day program will remain open until 4:30 this afternoon and be closed tomorrow. We will continue to communicate as information becomes available. Thank you for your continued support.

post_text:
Dear Parents and Community Members,

As we continue to take a proactive and precautionary approach, we have decided to cancel some larger scale school-related events so we can focus on keeping our buildings clean and healthy for student learning during the day. We will monitor these decisions as necessary; therefore, as of this date we are cancelling events through March 20, 2020. Again, we are actively communicating with our local health officials to guide us in our decision making. As we work through this challenge, please know we will provide updates as new information is available.

Please see the following events that will be cancelled and rescheduled if possible.

March 11th: Third Grade Recorder Concert, SES, 7 pm
March 13th: Fifth Grade Social, Pond, 7-9 pm
March 14th & 15th: FIRST Robotics Competition
March 16th: Attitudes in Reverse Parent Education Night for grades 7-12, RHS, 7 pm
March 18th: Child Assault Prevention Program for First Grade Parents, 7 pm
March 20th: Sixth Grade Social, Pond, 7-9 pm

As always, we thank you for your support and partnership.

A reminder on kindergarten registration.....

Kindergarten Registration for the 2020-2021 school year will take place in the Sharon School Main Office on the following dates and times:

Monday March 23rd 2:00pm to 7:00pm
Tuesday March 24th 2:00pm to 7:00pm
Wednesday March 25th 2:00pm to 7:00pm

Students must be 5 years old by October 1, 2020 to be eligible for entrance into Kindergarten. We do not make any exceptions. It is our obligation, purpose and passion to take care of the whole child socially, emotionally and academically.

Here is a link that we hope you find helpful as your family enters this exciting phase:
https://tinyurl.com/y3kl3zma

Here is a link to our registration page. Scroll down and follow Steps 1-3.
https://www.robbinsville.k12.nj.us/departments/central_registration/new_student_registration
